{
  "stem": "10587.3",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Jude, yeah.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Right.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was-- first I think there was the arm band, right, and then they changed it.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't know exactly when, but I think it came quickly after.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So-- and then also-- the Poles took advantage of it, too, because they could see-- many of them sided with the Germans.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they were-- as I said before, there was-- we knew that there was always some kind of anti-Semitism existing in Poland, but we-- but it was more in the open then, in the place where we lived.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so-- the Poles also-- there was a curfew.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And, of course, the Poles would turn Jews in [INAUDIBLE] run over to a city of [INAUDIBLE] or somebody, in the evening, at night time.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we couldn't-- we were limited to-- not limited-- we were forbidden to be on the street or go any place beyond the curfew time.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] And it was really the turning point of the city of Oswiecim, when it became Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] The Polish army, I understand, had a big camp just outside of Oswiecim, which was part of-- must've been part of Auschwitz-- Oswiecim.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they-- so the Germans when they turned-- they had a-- they had all the buildings that he made to turn this place into a concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I don't know if it was a division or it was a like, here in our country, in the United States, they are like-- I was stationed in the Fourth Army, when I was in the Army during the Korean War.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But maybe there they had-- I don't know what-- I was too young to really know what the setup was, but it was a large cavalry type of Army camp, which the-- the Germans turned into the-- to the place for the-- The stables became our homes when-- when I was in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 53
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] The-- so-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] this existed-- this-- we were in Auschwitz until 1949-- '41.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In the town, right.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We lived in the same place.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I-- I don't remember about food, there was-- somehow we had enough food, I think.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we did not take any-- any-- we didn't have anybody else living with us.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So the living conditions only changed that we were restricted to because of the curfew and also because you could not do certain things because you were Jewish.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Like Jude, you could not-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I think they confiscated all the Jewish businesses.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And turned them over to the Poles.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I remember that we stayed in the same apartment until we were resettled at that time in Sosnowiec in 1941.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't really remember.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "If-- maybe because we didn't really-- we did not have any like automobiles.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I'm sure you had to turn in, and they confiscated businesses, automobiles and-- and--",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, I-- I really don't know.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't-- I think that we-- I don't remember having the radio after that.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Maybe we were not allowed to listen to it, or maybe they took it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Or-- but I remember that we kept the gramophone, because-- this during that time, we-- my parents wanted all the friends of-- of my siblings, especially the older ones, to come to our place rather than they, because of the curfew, because they were concerned.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The Germans would also [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] beat up on you for no reason at all, hit you with a rifle, maybe kick you, or-- and say you, [INAUDIBLE] Jude.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And so that's why the concern was for them so to-- keep the family at home.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At that time, no.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I know that my brother did.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Romek.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Romek was beaten up, but he also-- he also used to go out and look for them by themselves.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They used to really beat the hell out of them by singly.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then he used to run, come home, and because he was very much, very angered about the whole situation.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he was like a daredevil.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A German soldier threw, you know, right inside his-- the back of his-- inside his shirt, and he was hurting very much.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So he came running home one time, and screaming.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But he-- he would-- he-- he would go out and during curfew, and the parents, he would say, he was going to see a cousin in the same building, but actually he-- he must have snuck out.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And-- because he was looking for them.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't think so.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't think at that time there was a resistance group in my hometown.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I heard that resistance groups may-- when-- when we moved to Sosnowiec.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
